tissueExpression.summary: Most normal tissues displayed moderate to strong nuclear and/or cytoplasmic positivity. Additional membranous staining was observed in respiratory epithelia, renal tubules, pancreatic ducts and fallopian tube. The liver and lung were weakly stained or negative.

Most normal tissues displayed moderate to strong nuclear and/or cytoplasmic positivity. Additional membranous staining was observed in respiratory epithelia, renal tubules, pancreatic ducts and fallopian tube. The liver and lung were weakly stained or negative.

Most malignant cells exhibited moderate nuclear and/or cytoplasmic positivity. A few cases of endometrial cancers along with occasional squamous cell carcinomas of cervix, duct carcinomas of breast and malignant melanomas were strongly stained. Several cases of gastric, renal and pancreatic cancers were weakly stained or negative.
